name: 1960's Rhinestone Disco Ball Pendant Necklace
description: 1960's rhinestone disco ball pendant on japanned chain. This oval bauble pendant features prong set olive green and orange rhinestones in varying sizes. The pendant hangs on one of the two chains. This statement necklace is in excellent condition. The necklace measures 24.5" long and the pendant measures 1" in diameter at the widest.

name: 1930's Early Plastic Ocean Blue Brooch
description: 1930's early plastic, ocean blue brooch.  The "gems" are individually prong set and open-backed. This piece is an unusual find from the era and has marvelous scale. It is in very good vintage condition. The diameter measures 3" across.

name: 1950's Victorian Revival Bracelet
description: 1950’s Victorian Revival bracelet with blue rhinestones and pearls. The blue rhinestones truly pop in this attention-grabbing piece. In excellent vintage condition, the bracelet measures 7.5” long by 1.5” tall. The large panels measure 1.5” by 1.5” and the smaller panels measure 0.8” by 1.5”.

name: Art Nouveau Floral Brass Bracelet
description: Art Nouveau gilt brass bracelet circa 1910.  This bracelet has five floral plaques which lead into a decorative box clasp. A true period piece, this bracelet measures 7.25” long. Five floral ovals measure 1.25” by 0.75” each. In gently used vintage condition with some minor wear to the gilt finish consistent with age.

name: Modernist Sterling Silver Pendant Necklace
description: Designer-signed, hand wrought, Modernist, sterling silver necklace featuring anthropomorphic pendant. Let his funny face bring a smile to your own. Signed "925" and "NCCD" on the back of the pendant. The pendant measures 1.5" width by 2" height, and the necklace measures 24" long.

name: Christian Dior Swimming Fish Brooch
description: Like a fish out of water that discovered some sparkle! This 1980’s Christian Dior fish brooch features clear rhinestones. In excellent vintage condition, this pin measures 2.5” at it’s widest and 1.25” at its tallest.

name: Arts & Crafts Period Belt Buckle
description: A belt buckle from the Arts & Crafts period (circa 1860-1910). This beautifully decorative two-piece buckle is ready for your leather, velvet ribbon, or textile of choice. Both panels of the buckle measure 2.25” wide for a total measurement of 4.5” at its widest and 2.9” at its tallest. In very good vintage condition.

name: 1930's Brass and Glass Cameo Necklace
description: 1930's brass and glass cameo necklace with a filigree box clasp. The cameo features the profile of a lovely lady with flowing tresses on a black background. In very good vintage condition. Measures 17" long with 1.5" drop.

name: Sparkly Rhinestone Bangle
description: 1980's brass bangle with sparkly rhinestones and glittery black resin. In gently used condition, this bracelet has some stones that present a bit darker than others and there are some minor dents in the brass, though nothing that takes away from its wearability, sparkle, or shine! Diameter measures 2.5" and width of bangle measures 1.375".

name: 1950's Pink Floral Rhinestone Suite
description: 1950’s sparkly floral rhinestone suite featuring brooch and clip earrings.  Faux pearls and hot pink rhinestones are prong-set and center rhinestones have an aurora borealis finish. In excellent vintage condition. The brooch has a diameter of 2". The earrings measure approximately 1" long and 1" wide.

name: 1960's Pop Art Arrow Belt
description: 1960’s mod, geometric, Lucite arrow belt buckle in red, pink, and black with a red elastic belt. In gently used vintage condition, with a small discoloration on elastic and some minor scratches to surface of arrow. Measures 23" unstretched and 27.5" stretched.

name: 1950's Phone Cord Purse
description: Ring ring! Playful, multi-colored phone cord purse in red, green, cream, and navy. Silk lined with interior pocket. Circa 1950’s and in gently used vintage condition. The bag measures 6" x 12.5" x 2".

name: 1960's J.Hull Hand-wrought Collar
description: 1960's J. Hull hand-wrought collar from Denmark with an amethyst druzy placed in the center. A gorgeous, bold piece. In very good vintage condition. The collar measures 3.75" wide with a height of .375". The center amethyst measures 1"w.

name: Unusual Miriam Haskell Red Cherries Necklace
description: Very unusual Miriam Haskell red cherries necklace. Created from round red glass beads, green seed beads, and bell caps.  A very fun piece with cherries cascading throughout, even off the filigree clasp.  Circa 1950. This necklace measures 16” in length and is in amazing condition.

name: 1920's Rhinestone Drop Necklace
description: Elegant 1920's prong-set rhinestone necklace with seven larger rhinestone drops hanging from center. In very good vintage condition with some wear to the plating on the back, consistent with age. The necklace measures 14.5" long and the center drop measures .875"h by 25"w.

name: 1950's "Take A Gamble With Your Heart" Bracelet
description: Heart charm bracelet from the late 1950's with miniature dice caged inside heart. Totally whimsical and unusual--take a gamble with your heart and on this very unique bracelet. In very good condition. Charm pendant measures 1.25"h x 1"w and dangles from 7" chain.

name: 1950's Black and White Rhinestone Earrings
description: 1950's dangly fringe earrings featuring prong-set, black and white rhinestones. These earrings have great movement and would be tons of fun for an evening out. These earrings are in excellent condition and measure 3.5"h by 875"w.

name: 1950's Cleopatra Bib Necklace
description: 1950's Cleopatra bib necklace with a gold chain and faux pearl, crystal, and aurora borealis rhinestone beads in excellent vintage condition. Channel Liz Taylor in her prime. This necklace is in excellent condition and has a 2.5" drop and the length can be adjusted from 14" to 18.5".

name: 1950's Giant Daisy Rhinestone Brooch
description: 1950's giant sparkly daisy brooch featuring individually prong set rhinestones in greens, yellows, and orange, in japanned metal. You will definitely turn some heads with this fantastic statement piece. In very good vintage condition. Measures 4.5"w by 2.5"h.

name: Wachenheimer Sterling Silver Art Deco Bracelet
description: "Wachenheimer" sterling silver Art Deco bracelet from Germany. The reflective oval onyx and marcasite detail will add beautiful glimmer to your wrist. The bracelet is in excellent condition and measures 7" long with a width of 0.75".

name: 1960's Multi-chain Pendant Necklace
description: This 1960's four strand necklace features green rhinestones, filigree and tassel pendants. Multi-chain dressing is the latest trend and here it is done for you. This necklace is in excellent vintage condition. Strand 1 measures 18" with 1"h x .625"w pendant; Strand 2, 24" with 1.5"h x .5"w pendant; Strand 3, 30" chain with 3"h x 1"w pendant; Strand 4, 40" chain.

name: 14K Filigree Art Deco Bracelet
description: A beautiful and ornate 14K white gold, filigree, 1920's Art Deco bracelet  features a diamond center and 2 trillion cut emerald-tone paste stones and is in excellent vintage condition. The emerald paste adds a touch of color to this beautiful bracelet. The bracelet is in excellent condition and measures 7" long. The centerpiece measures 1.125"w x .5625"h.

name: 1920's 14K Gold Lavalier Necklace
description: A classic, 1920's, 14K white gold, filigree, lavalier necklace featuring a lovely little diamond center. As with many true pieces of this era, the back of this lavalier is yellow gold. This elegant necklace is in excellent vintage condition and is a piece that you can wear forever. The pendant measures 1.5"h x .25"w and hangs on a 16" chain.

name: 80's Lucite Earrings
description: Oh so fun, 80’s Lucite Earrings! Not for the faint of heart, these 4” earrings feature bright orange, pink, and magenta foil-backed Lucite cabochons on clear Lucite background.  They are in good vintage condition; however there is one nick in the clear Lucite on the top circle.  In my humble opinion, it does not detract from these electric earrings.

name: 1920’s Czech Glass Flapper Necklace
description: This silvertone pendant necklace features a bezel set clear Czech glass in a filigree frame. The pendant has a beautiful antique patina. This piece is in very good vintage condition. The chain measures 32” and the pendant is 2.25” by 1” at its widest point. Put on this necklace and do the Charleston.

name: Eisenberg Rhinestone Suite
description: Eisenberg rhinestone bracelet and earrings.  Signed EISENBERG in block letters. Sets like these were seen on the likes of actresses such as Rita Hayworth. This particular set dates to the late 1940’s or early 1950’s. The bracelet measures 6.75”  long. The clip earrings measure 1.25” long. Both bracelet and earrings are in excellent vintage condition.

name: 1940’s Lisner Festoon Necklace
description: 1940’s Lisner gilt brass festoon necklace. This piece has a chrysanthemum center with a hanging tassel. Certainly inspired by the festoon necklaces of the Victorian period. This piece is in excellent vintage condition.  The interior chain measures 15” and the drop measures 2.5".

name: 14K Gold Chalice Earrings
description: Fun 1940's 14K gold screwback earrings in the shape of a chalice.

name: 1940’s 14K Rose Gold Floral Bracelet
description: This 1940’s 14K rose gold bracelet consists of flowers that feature sapphires, rubies, emeralds, and a few diamond centers.  The bracelet is comprised of 5 hinged arched panels, and closes with a hinge pin attached with a delicate chain and seed pearls. This bracelet is in excellent condition and the diameter measures 2.5".

name: Christian Dior Sunflower Necklace/Brooch and Matching Earrings
description: Christian Dior sunflower necklace/brooch and matching earrings from the 80’s. These sunflowers consist of a large oval citrine-toned rhinestone center and petals of clear rhinestones. This suite is in excellent vintage condition. The sunflower pendant hangs from a 21" chain and measures 2" by 2" and is removable; it can be worn as a brooch.  The clip earrings are 1.5" long by 1.25" wide.

name: Hobé Festoon Brass and Garnet Necklace
description: A marvelous Hobé festoon necklace in brass with bezel set garnet glass.  The larger cabachons are half round, while the smaller bezel set pieces have a flat cut.  This 40’s piece has an obvious Victorian design inspiration.  In excellent vintage condition, this necklace measures 15.5”.

name: Red and Black 1980's Crystal Clip Earrings
description: A showstopping pair of red and black crystal clip earrings signed "Bellini by FormArt" from the 1980’s. The Swarovski crystals are all affixed to black resin or plastic. Take these earring to the theater; they are dying to see Chicago. In excellent vintage condition, they measure 3.5" long by 1" at widest.

name: Victorian 14K Gold, Pearl and Onyx Festoon Necklace
description: Victorian 14K gold festoon necklace created with onyx and pearls. This lovely number is ornate, delicate and detailed, yet easy to wear--the essence of Victorian jewelry.  In excellent vintage condition, the chain measures 16" and the festoons drop 0.75". The center pendant is 0.85" by 2" long.

name: 1940’s Giant Rhinestone & Givre Glass Brooch
description: 1940’s giant rhinestone and givre glass brooch signed "Austria". In various shades of green from emerald to peridot, and a spattering of blue. All stones are prong set. Some of the rhinestones have a coating of aurora borealis. It’s a showstopper measuring 5” across and 1 ¼” at its widest length.   In very good vintage condition, however it appears that the pin catch was replaced sometime ago with a gold-tone lock.

name: 1950's Pearl Tassel Dusters
description: These screwback earrings have a floral top. Several pearl tassels dangle from a rhinestone bell cap. These earrings are in excellent vintage condition and measure 4.75" long and 1.25" at widest.

name: 1930's Art Deco Celluloid Necklace
description: 1930’s Art Deco long green celluloid daisy necklace.  Think spring!  This piece is in excellent vintage condition. The chain measures 34" and the pendant measures 2.5" at longest and 2.25" at widest.

name: 1940’s “Think Spring” Coral Celluloid Necklace
description: 11 charming coral celluloid flowers hang from an 18" celluloid chain. All the findings are brass.  Flowers measure 1.15" in diameter. This piece is in good vintage condition.  The only flaw is a small chip in one flower petal that is incredibly difficult to notice, because all of the dangling flowers overlap each other.

name: Victorian 10K Rose Gold Sardonyx Carnelian Cameo Man’s Ring
description: Victorian 10K rose gold sardonyx carnelian cameo man’s ring. The ring shank is designed to appear like an ancient column. The cameo profile is that of a gentleman warrior, sporting a period style moustache, with his battle gear and helmet. This piece can certainly be worn by a man or a woman. It is in very good vintage condition, with the tiniest of flea bites on one corner, really only visible with a jewelers loupe. The ring size is 8.75. The cameo measures 0.75" long by 0.5" wide.

name: 1930's 18K Gold Engraved Coral Cameo Ring
description: 1930's 18K gold engraved coral cameo ring. This coral woman is gorgeously carved and prong set on an engraved and stippled plaque. I love the unusually large scale of this cameo ring.  It is hallmarked 750 inside the shank.  This ring is in excellent vintage condition. The ring size is 8.5. The cameo measures 1.25" long, 0.75" at its widest and is 0.375" high.

name: Eisenberg 60's Clip Earrings
description: 1960’s Eisenberg rhinestone clip earrings in the classic 60’s colors tan, brown, and clear.  The larger stones are prong set.  These earrings are in excellent vintage condition and measure 1" long and 0.5" wide

name: 1940’s Trifari Crown Brooch
description: 1940’s Trifari crown brooch. This classic brooch has the early crown Trifari hallmark.  It features prong set glass cabochons and round and baguette rhinestones.  It is in excellent vintage condition and measures 0.75" long by 0.75" wide.
